</b></p>
<p>71. JUA 15/11/11   Case no.: CHN 22/2011   State Reply: 30/01/12   <b>Alleged abduction 
of human rights defender. 
</b></p>
<p>72. JUA1 22/09/11   Case no.: CHN 24/2010   State Reply: 16/02/11   <b>Alleged detention 
of HIV/AIDS activist. 
</b></p>
<p><b>Observations 
</b></p>
<p>73. The Special Rapporteur wishes to express her deep concern about the arrest, 
detention and intimidation of human rights defenders in China for peacefully exercising 
their right to freedom of expression. In this regard, she wishes to remind the Government of 
the People&#8217;s Republic of China of the provisions of the Declaration on Human Rights 
</p>
<p>Defenders, specifically article 2, article 6, points b) and c), and article 12. 
</p>
<p>74. The Special Rapporteur is also concerned about information she has received about 
increased restrictions on the freedom of peaceful assembly and the negative impact such 
restrictions have had on the work of human rights defenders. In this regard, she would like 
to call the attention of the Government to article 5, point a), of the Declaration on Human 
Rights Defenders, as well as the report of the former Special Representative of the 
Secretary General on the situation of human rights defenders to the General Assembly in 
2006 (A/61/312), para. 98.<b> 
</b></p>
<p>75. The Special Rapporteur reiterates her hope that the Government will respond 
favourably to her repeated requests since 2008 to visit the country.<b> 
</b></p>
