<p><b>  Observations 
</b></p>
<p>212. The Special Rapporteur thanks the Government of the Kyrgyz Republic for its 
extensive response transmitted to her communication regarding due process rights and 
guarantees in the conduct of criminal proceedings in relation to the June 2010 violence. She 
commends the Government for the enquiries conducted and measures taken in this regard, 
but she remains concerned about intimidation, threats and judicial harassment of human 
rights defenders in relation to the events of June 2010. The Special Rapporteur expresses 
grave concern with regard to the case of Mr. Azimjan Askarov, who has been sentenced to 
life in prison by the Supreme Court for crimes in relation to these events, amid grave 
concerns about lack of due process. In this context, the Special Rapporteur would like to 
remind the Government of the provisions contained in the Declaration on Human Rights 
Defenders, notably its articles 2, 9 and 12. The Special Rapporteur remains available to 
provide any technical assistance the Government of the Kyrgyz Republic might require.  
