<p><b>  Observations 
</b></p>
<p>219. The Special Rapporteur regrets that, at the time of the finalization of the current 
report, the Government of Libya (Libyan Arab Jamahiriya at the time the communications 
were sent) had not submitted a response to any of the communications sent by her during 
the reporting period. While recognizing that the country is faced with a very different 
situation compared to when the communications in question were sent, the Special 
Rapporteur calls on the Government of Libya to ensure a conducive working environment 
for human rights defenders in compliance with the Declaration on Human Rights 
Defenders, where their psychological and physical integrity is ensured, and where they do 
not face acts of harassment and intimidation. The Special Rapporteur urges the Government 
to pay particular attention to the situation of human rights defenders in the context of 
elections planned for 2012. She remains available to provide any technical assistance the 
Government of Libya might require. 
</p>
