<p><b>  Observations 
</b></p>
<p>225. The Special Rapporteur remains deeply concerned about the situation of human 
rights defenders in Malawi, particularly with regard to restrictions on their rights to 
freedom of assembly and freedom of expression. She notes with concern that human rights 
defenders who have exercised these rights have been met with violent attacks by security 
forces and other actors, resulting in injuries and even deaths of defenders. The Special 
Rapporteur urges the Government of Malawi to pay close attention to the provisions 
contained in the Declaration on Human Rights Defenders, notably its article 2, article 5, 
point a), article 6, points b) and c), and article 12. She also calls on the Government to 
revisit the recommendations put forward by the former Special Representative of the 
Secretary General on the situation of human rights defenders in her report to the General 
Assembly in 2006 (A/61/312, para. 98). The Special Rapporteur remains available to 
provide any technical assistance the Government might require. 
</p>
