<p>228. The Special Rapporteur wishes to express her continued concern for human rights 
defenders advocating for minority rights in the country. According to information she has 
received, this group continues to face arbitrary arrests and violent threats, as well as 
restrictions to their rights to freedom of assembly and freedom of expression. The Special 
Rapporteur would like to remind the Government of Malaysia of the provisions contained 
in the Declaration on Human Rights Defenders, notably its articles 2, 5, point a), 6, points 
b) and c), and 12. 
</p>
<p>229. The Special Rapporteur has followed the development of the new Peaceful 
Assembly Bill and has previously expressed her related concerns.3 She would like to refer 
the Government of Malaysia to the recommendations put forward  by the former Special 
Representative of the Secretary General on the situation of human rights defenders in her 
reports to the General Assembly in 2006 (A/61/312, para. 98) and 2007 (A/62/225, para. 
101). 
