<p><b>  Myanmar 
</b></p>
<p>259. JUA 26/07/11   Case no.: MMR 2/2011   State Reply: 19/09/11   <b>Alleged 
incommunicado detention of political prisoner. </b> 
</p>
<p>260. JUA 28/11/11   Case no.: MMR 4/2011   State Reply: None to date   <b>Alleged 
assault of a prisoner by prison guards.</b> 
</p>
<p><b>  Observations 
</b></p>
<p>261. The Special Rapporteur commends the Government of Myanmar for its recent 
efforts aimed at democratic reform, which she hopes will lead to a conducive working 
environment for human rights defenders. However, she expresses concern about the 
situation of human rights defenders in Myanmar and urges the Government to put in place 
measures to ensure their physical and psychological integrity, in accordance with articles 2 
and 12 of the Declaration on Human Rights Defenders. This pertains in particular to prisons 
and detention facilities where human rights defenders are being held.  
</p>
<p>262. The Special Rapporteur is also concerned about restrictions in place with regard to 
freedom of expression, which is a considerable impediment to the work of human rights 
defenders in Myanmar. She would like to draw to the attention of  the Government the 
provisions contained in the Declaration on Human Rights Defenders in this regard, 
specifically article 6, points b) and c). 
</p>
