<p>307. The Special Rapporteur would like to express her deep concern about the context of 
increasing harassment, threats and acts of violence against human rights defenders in the 
Russian Federation, in particular against journalists and lawyers. She is also concerned </p>

<p><b>A/HRC/19/55/Add.2 
</b></p>
<p><b>36</b>  
</p>
<p>about reported arrests, detentions and instances of police abuse, excessive use of force 
during demonstrations and judicial harassment against human rights defenders. In this 
regard, she wishes to call to the attention of the Government the provisions contained in the 
Declaration on Human Rights Defenders, notably article 5, point a), article 9 and article 12. 
On the issue of the right to freedom of peaceful assembly, she encourages the Government 
to revisit the recommendations given by the former Special Representative of the Secretary 
General on the situation of human rights defenders in her report to the General Assembly in 
2006 (A/61/312, para. 98).<b> 
</b></p>
<p>308. The Special Rapporteur is also concerned about increased obstacles for defenders of 
LGBTI rights as a result of legislative moves in some cities in the Russian Federation, 
which would represent considerable restrictions on their rights to freedom of expression 
and freedom of assembly. In this regard, the Special Rapporteur urges the Russian 
Federation to ensure rights protected under article 6, points b) and c), and article 7 of the 
Declaration on Human Rights Defenders are respected.<b> 
